.TH "CUSTOMELEMENTREGISTRY.UPGRADE" "3JS" "February 23, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CustomElementRegistry.upgrade \- CustomElementRegistry: upgrade() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]upgrade()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] interface upgrades all
shadow\-containing custom elements in a \f[CR]Node\f[R] subtree, even
before they are connected to the main document.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
upgrade(root)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]root\f[R]
A \f[CR]Node\f[R] instance with shadow\-containing descendant elements
to upgrade.
If there are no descendant elements that can be upgraded, no error is
thrown.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH DESCRIPTION
When an HTML element is parsed or created, it may use a tag name that
corresponds to a custom element (e.g., \f[CR]<my\-element>\f[R]).
If the custom element\(cqs class has not yet been registered with the
appropriate \f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] at the time the element is
created, the element exists as an undefined, plain
\f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R].
It looks and behaves like any unknown element \(em it has no special
behavior, lifecycle callbacks, or custom prototype methods.
.PP
\f[B]Upgrading\f[R] is the process of retroactively promoting such an
element to a full\-fledged custom element once its definition becomes
available.
When an element is upgraded:
.IP "1." 3
Its prototype is swapped to the custom element class that was registered
with \f[CR]define()\f[R].
.IP "2." 3
Its \f[CR]connectedCallback()\f[R] and any other applicable lifecycle
callbacks are invoked.
.IP "3." 3
If the class defines \f[CR]observedAttributes\f[R], the
\f[CR]attributeChangedCallback()\f[R] is called for each attribute that
already has a value.
.PP
Normally, elements are upgraded automatically when their definition is
registered via \f[CR]define()\f[R], but only if they are already
connected to the document.
The \f[CR]upgrade()\f[R] method is useful when you need to upgrade
elements that exist in a disconnected DOM subtree (for example, elements
created via \f[CR]Document.createElement()\f[R] or parsed into a
\f[CR]DocumentFragment\f[R]) before they are inserted into the document.
.SH EXAMPLES
Taken from the \c
.UR https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/custom-elements.html#dom-customelementregistry-upgrade
HTML spec
.UE \c
:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] el = document.createElement(\(dqspider\-man\(dq);

\f[B]class\f[R] SpiderMan \f[B]extends\f[R] HTMLElement {}
customElements.define(\(dqspider\-man\(dq, SpiderMan);

console.assert(!(el \f[B]instanceof\f[R] SpiderMan)); \f[I]// not yet upgraded\f[R]

customElements.upgrade(el);
console.assert(el \f[B]instanceof\f[R] SpiderMan); \f[I]// upgraded!\f[R]
.EE
